## DESCRIPTION

> Mscgen is a small program that parses Message Sequence Chart descriptions and produces images as the output. Message Sequence Charts (MSCs) are a way of representing entities and interactions over some time period. This program and the language it parses have been inspired by Graphviz Dot, which provides a really good way to document State Transition Diagrams, data structures and directed graphs.
> http://www.mcternan.me.uk/mscgen/index.html
## STEPS TO REPRODUCE

Input any msc source, for example

```
# MSC for some fictional process
msc {
  hscale = "2";

  a,b,c;

  a->b [ label = "ab()" ] ;
  b->c [ label = "bc(TRUE)"];
  c=>c [ label = "process(1)" ];
  c=>c [ label = "process(2)" ];
  ...;
  c=>c [ label = "process(n)" ];
  c=>c [ label = "process(END)" ];
  a<<=c [ label = "callback()"];
  ---  [ label = "If more to run", ID="*" ];
  a->a [ label = "next()"];
  a->c [ label = "ac1()\nac2()"];
  b<-c [ label = "cb(TRUE)"];
  b->b [ label = "stalled(...)"];
