The `av` and `v` members of GD_rank are assigned in `allocate_ranks` in mincross.c:

```c
    GD_rank(g)[r].av = GD_rank(g)[r].v = N_NEW(cn[r] + 1, node_t *);
```

In `make_vn_slot` in flat.c, `v` can be reallocted, but `av` is not updated, leaving it dangling:

```c
    v = GD_rank(g)[r].v =
       ALLOC(GD_rank(g)[r].n + 2, GD_rank(g)[r].v, node_t *);
```

In `dot_cleanup_graph` in dotinit.c, the allocation is cleaned up, but `av` is used for this:

```c
    free(GD_rank(g)[i].av);
```

If `av` had been reallocated before this, then this will free the wrong address.  Also if `av` is used after the reallocate, it could potentially corrupt something else that had been assigned the address.

